<div id='communityQuestionsWithAnswers'>
<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/417788-i-m-familiar-with-internet-shaming-and">I&#39;m familiar with internet-shaming, and mostly interested in &quot;What Next?&quot; questions. e.g., what recourse do &quot;shamed&quot; people have; can effective counter-campaigns be mounted; are there different &quot;systems&quot; of social media where shaming wouldn&#39;t be so encouraged.

Does this book address questions like these? Does it have interesting answers? Or is it mostly the case studies of specific shaming incidents?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_417788'><a id="like_count_community_question_417788" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/417788?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">5 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F22571552-so-you-ve-been-publicly-shamed">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
