<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/382091-how-do-you-feel-about-the-public-shaming">How do you feel about the public shaming of newscaster Brian Williams? Personally, I think he got some scary dreams mixed up with reality until the memory of the dream scenes took over from the memory of the literal actions. It could happen to anyone. What do you think? When this happens to a public figure, how might this be better handled than a public sensationalist shaming?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_382091'><a id="like_count_community_question_382091" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/382091?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">2 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F22571552-so-you-ve-been-publicly-shamed">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/382091-how-do-you-feel-about-the-public-shaming">6 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/382091-how-do-you-feel-about-the-public-shaming">See all 5 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/27533769-benny-thomas"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1389331629i/27533769.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/27533769-benny-thomas">Benny Thomas</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Brian Williams is not an ordinary citizen. He is an anchor and as such, people look to him for unbiased, factual perspectives. In his case, the public<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Brian Williams is not an ordinary citizen. He is an anchor and as such, people look to him for unbiased, factual perspectives. In his case, the public shaming is actually performing socially useful tasks - one, it reinforces the value of good journalism and two, it serves as a warning to other journalists. In <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
